HEADWORD: Orthocenter
<hw>Or`tho*cen"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + <ets>center</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>
<def>That point in which the three perpendiculars let fall from the
angles of a triangle upon the opposite sides, or the sides produced,
mutually intersect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthoceras</ent>⟦br⟧
